als as I don't have A: DoI, and Iceflame doesn't work, to my knowledge, on Draught of E`ci.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Maybe I'm not getting something, but why does there tend to be such a shunning of Iceflame + ISoS (NOT necessarily A:DoI)?<br>
<br>
As far as I can tell it's very good..<br>
ISoS + Iceflame = 1200 dmg times a max of 30% increase = 1560 damage for 300 mana. That is a ratio of 5.2 - far better than any single target spell we receive. ever.<br>
<br>
However, Iceflame gives a 30% <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>maximum</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> - so - if the average damage increase per cast is even as low as, say, 15%, ISoS will still yield 1380 damage for 300 mana: a ratio of 4.6: still better than anything we ever receive.<br>
<br>
Why do people not like it...? <p><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="font-size:xx-small;"><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=630472" target="top">Oaklenia Somesweetlastname, Sorcerer of Karana</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
